@mgaido91 Hey, actually feels like it is done, the only problem with testing I faced is that my implicit extension for the Kubernetest client blocks me from testing SparkKubernetesApp monitoring thread. Maybe anyone has ideas on how to handle it?

@igorcalabria , @arunmahadevan , @lukatera , what do you think on finalizing that PR and pushing it forward?

In the whole this code os already running in multiple projects, so seems like it is worth to push. As well I plan to open 2 follow-up PRs:
- Helm chart for Livy
- Docs on Running livy on Kubernetes for Livy web-site

@jahstreet : We currently run spark in standalone mode on a kubernetes cluster with HPA (horizontal pod scaler) and have incubator-livy submit jobs to that . We are in the process of moving to spark native on K8s.

Does this PR use the modified spark-submit api that support Kubernetes (http://spark.apache.org/docs/latest/running-on-kubernetes.html#client-mode) or does it need the spark-operator (https://github.com/GoogleCloudPlatform/spark-on-k8s-operator).

Apologies, I was not able to gather this piece of information from the PR.

@pkrishn6 It uses Spark as is, you don't need to do any modifications to the Spark code. It uses Spark Submit in [cluster mode](http://spark.apache.org/docs/latest/running-on-kubernetes.html#cluster-mode), well, you can submit a job in a client mode too, but it will not work with Livy as you expect it I guess. It doesn't need spark-operator either.

In short: you POST JSON to Livy -> Livy does Spark Submit in cluster mode for you

Strongly recommend to try in your case. You may be interested in that [Helm](https://github.com/jahstreet/spark-on-kubernetes-helm) which contains some descriptions as well.

@runzhiwang I see you point. On the other side, actually we are returning a string in that case, so if you write some automatic code which uses the metadata to choose what to do, ie. `getString`, etc.etc. This would not work with decimal.

I would suggest then to:
 - improve this PR description, which currently says nothing, explaining the issue, the expected behavior and so on;
 - introduce a configuration flag for switching between the current status and you new behavior.

Thanks.

@mgaido91 Hi, thank you for the suggestions. 

1.  I have improve this PR description.

2.  This configuration flag maybe is not necessary. Even with this PR, getString() can still get the value of decimal, and the api is compatible.

@runzhiwang regarding the description of the PR: I don0t see how point 3 is relevant for this PR The behavior would be the same in that case, wouldn't it?

> I think the original behavior is kind of bug(e.g. return decimal type as string).

I think this is arguable: what does Livy return for that column? A string. What does that column contain? A decimal. Hence both answers are correct somehow: one refers to what is returned to the client, the other to how data is stored in the table/backend. For this reason, I think having a flag which lets the user customize/choose the more appropriate behavior to him is the best option.
